{"clause_type": "uncapped liability", "summary": "The clause means:

- Any legal claims related to the agreement must be started within two years, except for specific obligations and payments.
- Both parties agree not to claim punitive or exemplary damages (which are meant to punish or make an example of the other party) and can only recover actual damages they've suffered."}

{"clause_type": "parties", "summary": ""The Landlord agrees to provide the Tenant with the keys to the Property on the first day of the lease term, and the Tenant agrees to return all keys to the Landlord on the last day of the lease term. If the Tenant does not return all keys, the Tenant will pay for the cost of changing the locks on all the doors at the Property."

Summary:
The landlord will give the tenant the keys to the property when the lease starts. The tenant must return all keys when the lease ends. If the tenant doesn't return all the keys, they will have to pay to have the locks changed."}

{"clause_type": "uncapped liability", "summary": "The clause says that:

1. No party will be responsible for indirect damages like lost profits, except for breaches of confidentiality, license agreements, or amounts owed to third parties as described in the indemnity section.
2. If something goes wrong, the most a party can be liable for is the amount paid or payable by that party in the 12 months before the issue arose."}

{"clause_type": "minimum commitment", "summary": "If the Reseller sells less than half of the agreed annual target, Todos can either:

(a) end the Reseller's exclusive rights and start selling the Products themselves or through others, while allowing the Reseller to continue selling non-exclusively, or

(b) end the agreement entirely if the Reseller doesn't meet the 50% sales target within 180 days of notice."}

